      public static final java.lang.String getSectionName​(org.apache.uima.jcas.JCas pJCas, org.apache.uima.jcas.tcas.Annotation pAnnotation)
      getSectionName retrieves the section that this annotation sits within. There is a hierarchy of what kind of section labels returned. If the annotation already has the section labeled, pass this along. If there is a geographical section* this is embedded within, the geographical section name is returned. If there is no geographical section, the CEM section name is returned. A geographical section is a section where the section name returned from the Sectionizer corresponds to the contentHeading found in the text.
      Parameters:
      pJCas - the j cas
      pAnnotation - the annotation
      Returns:
      String
